Description: Harmoney is a mobile app that manages communication, regulating chores, and splitting household expenses for all types of shared living
Headquarters Regions: Greater Seattle Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: As a college student and then as a young professional, the cheapest way to find urban housing is to live with roommates. We know from first hand that complications and irritations can arise in these situations, and we've found it's mostly due to a lack of system and communication channels. So, we're developing Harmoney, a mobile app promotes respectful living within a shared house. Harmoney does this by managing communication, organizing chores, and splitting finances among roommates. With dorm/rent costs skyrocketing and jobs difficult to obtain, the number of college aged and young professionals choosing to live in shared housing is growing, as is the length of time people spend in these situations. There are apps on the market that help manage different particular sides of shared living, but we feel like there still is no comprehensive tool out there that is widely used. That's why we're bringing all aspects of roommate life together with payment, chore, calendar, and messaging tabs.  Our app and web counterpart is applicable for college shared houses, fraternities, young professionals, couples, families, and more.

Full Description: The California Municipal Finance Authority’s (“CMFA”) mission is to support economic development, job creation and social programs throughout the State of California while giving back to California communities. The CMFA shares 25% of all issuance fees directly with its member communities. In addition, a grant equal to 25% of the issuance fee is made to the California Foundation for Stronger Communities (“CFSC”) to fund charities designated by the member communities. A portion of the annual fees received by the CMFA will also be directed to charitable activities within California communities. This unique commitment to “give back” directly to the communities in which we operate sets the CMFA apart.

Full Description: BDCM stands directly in the path of the booming demand for outsourced administration services in the financial services industry. By outsourcing their back office support services to us, their clients can reduce costs and concentrate on what they do best: marketing, servicing clients and managing investment portfolios.     BDCM was originally formed to provide outsourced support services for 5 sister financial service companies. By word of mouth, other hedge funds, investment advisors, financial planners and insurance agencies have expressed interest in BDCM's administrative services for their firms. This is when they realized BDCM is positioned to cash in on this explosive trend.     By raising working capital, BDCM can capture a larger share of the strong demand for their services. They plan to grow both organically and by acquisition.     Equity Net’s business plan analysis projects BDCM’s pre-money valuation at $13,921,625 based on competitive cash-flow discounting using the median IRR of their peer group.    Equity Net estimates an annual rate of return for investors of 75.9% with investors cashing out their profits in three to five years. Description: Revolutionary pixels for tomorrow's OLED displays
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: The nVerpix's Organic Light Emitting Transistor enables the cost-effective manufacturing of OLED displays: - Solves the "OLED backplane problem" by simplifying the sub-pixel to just two components (typically >8). - Ultra-simple 2-TFT pixel architecture improves manufacturing yields and lowers costs. - The fundamentally new transistor architecture is highly stable to bias, temperature, and illumination stress instabilities -> a problem for ALL conventional transistors. - Vertical architecture allows for high-aperture ratio pixels -> better image, longer lifetimes. - Compatible with all form-factors (especially beneficial for large-area and flexible/transparent displays)
